# Must restart session (log out and log back in) to make windrbd
drive visible in Explorer (it is visible in cmd and cygwin shell
rightaway).

--------------------------------------------------------------------------

Flush requests are not propagated to backing device.

Auto-promote is not supported.

Right now only NTFS is supported atop the windrbd device.

System Volume (C:) cannot be used for windrbd.

No 32-Bit version is supported, only 64 bit.

On installation (or upgrade) a system reboot is required.

Windows 7 is minimum (no Vista, no XP) (SP1 required (?))

Setting sendtimeout (via netconf / timeout) is not supported

Setting send buffer size (via netconf / sndbuf-size) is not supported
